<paragraph id="D36136DFFFE7FFEDFF0EFAA3FC148D81" blockId="3.[151,1437,1319,1532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE7FFEDFF0EFAA3FEDF8D3C" bold="true" box="[151,335,1319,1345]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Identification:</emphasis>
Forewing length 9.0–10.5 mm. 
<taxonomicName id="14DE4D5CFFE7FFEDFD4EFAACFC758D3C" box="[727,997,1320,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candefacta">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE7FFEDFD4EFAACFC758D3C" box="[727,997,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ponometia candefacta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a white forewing with a brown, fused medial and postmedial lines, and a prominent round, gray reniform spot that is outlined in white. There can be some faint yellow scales proximal to the reniform spot between the brown costal spot and brown band. The orbicular spot is a tiny black dot. The prominent reniform spot distinguishes it from 
<taxonomicName id="14DE4D5CFFE7FFEDFB73FA1CFE828DAA" authority="Guenee" authorityName="Guenee" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erastrioides">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE7FFEDFB73FA1CFA0C8DCC" box="[1258,1436,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">P. erastrioides</emphasis>
(Guenée)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="14DE4D5CFFE7FFEDFE86FA39FDAD8DAB" box="[287,573,1469,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candefacta">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE7FFEDFE86FA39FDAD8DAB" box="[287,573,1469,1494]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ponometia candefacta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="14DE4D5CFFE7FFEDFDE7FA39FC288DAA" authority="Guenee" authorityName="Guenee" box="[638,952,1469,1495]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erastrioides">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE7FFEDFDE7FA39FCA98DAB" box="[638,825,1469,1494]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">P. erastrioides</emphasis>
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE7FFEDFCDBFA39FCDC8DAA" bold="true" box="[834,844,1469,1495]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">(</emphasis>
Guenée
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE7FFEDFC34FA39FC288DAA" bold="true" box="[941,952,1469,1495]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are considered to be congeneric with 
<taxonomicName id="14DE4D5CFFE7FFEDFF0EFA67FCEF8D81" authority="Herrich-Schaffer 1868 (Poole and Lafontaine 2010)" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer 1868 (Poole and Lafontaine" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,895,1506,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Ponometia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E1AAEACDFFE7FFEDFF0EFA67FE868D81" box="[151,278,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Ponometia</emphasis>
Herrich-Schäffer 
<number id="651624F8FFE7FFEDFE73FA66FDB58D81" box="[490,549,1506,1532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1868.0">1868</number>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B74F4B2EFFE7FFEDFDADFA66FCE88D81" author="Poole" box="[564,888,1506,1532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="16" refString="Lafontaine, J. D. &amp; Poole, R. W. (2010) Review of the New World genera of the Subfamily Acontiinae (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae). ZooKeys, 39, 137 - 160." type="journal article" year="2010">
